The paper discusses the development of an intelligent pre-assessment system using student modelling and agent classified rules learning. This involves the use of artificial intelligence and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the cs.AI and cs.LG sub-categories. The system is also designed to improve human-computer interaction, which falls under the cs.HC sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of computational experimentation and graph visualisation, which could be associated with the cs.CY sub-category. Finally, the system is evaluated based on its performance, which could be related to the cs.IR sub-category.
